-- Lazio Moves Atop Italy's Serie A After Victory; Valencia Leads in Spain
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2010-10-03T22:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-26/lazio-joins-inter-milan-at-top-of-italy-s-serie-a-valencia-leads-in-spain.html
Lazio went top of Italian soccer’s
Serie A with a 1-0 home win over Brescia.  Stefano Mauri got the goal just before halftime yesterday.
Inter Milan trails by two points after drawing 0-0 with Juventus
in the late match.  Napoli is alongside Inter on 11 points after a 2-0 home win
over Roma. Marek Hamsik opened the scoring and Roma’s Juan put
through his own goal. AC Milan also has 11 points.  In Spain, Valencia leads the standings on 16 points after a
2-1 victory over Athletic Bilbao two days ago. Villarreal is a
point further back after a 2-0 win over Racing Santander
yesterday. Barcelona has 13 points after a 1-1 draw with Real
Mallorca, one point less than third-placed Real Madrid, which
beat Deportivo La Coruna 6-1 in yesterday’s late game.  In Germany, Mainz leads the standings after a record-
equaling start to the season, a 4-2 win over Hoffenheim giving
it a perfect seven straight victories. Bayern Munich lost 2-0 at
second-placed Borussia Dortmund yesterday, its third loss in
seven league games. Lucas Barrios and Nuri Sahin scored.  Rennes moved one point clear at the top of the French
standings with a 3-1 win over Toulouse in last night’s late
game. Saint Etienne is second with 17 points after a 1-1 draw
with Marseille two days ago.  In the Netherlands, PSV Eindhoven, a 3-0 winner over VVV-
Venlo yesterday, went top after Ajax lost 2-1 at home to
Utrecht. PSV has 18 points, with Ajax on 17.  WEEKEND RESULTS
===============  Italy: Udinese 1-0 Cesena 0; Parma 0-1 AC Milan; Lecce 1-0
Catania; Bologna 1-1 Sampdoria; Chievo 0-0 Cagliari; Fiorentina
1-2 Palermo; Genoa 2-1 Bari; Lazio 1-0 Brescia; Napoli 2-0 Roma;
Inter Milan 0-0 Juventus.  Spain: Real Zaragoza 2-2 Sporting Gijon; Real Sociedad 1-0
Espanyol; Valencia 2-1 Athletic Bilbao; Sevilla 3-1 Atletico
Madrid; Villarreal 2-0 Racing Santander; Almeria 1-1 Malaga;
Osasuna 1-1 Levante; Getafe 3-0 Hercules; Barcelona 1-1 Real
Mallorca; Real Madrid 6-1 Deportivo La Coruna.  Germany: Hanover 0-1 St Pauli; Freiburg 3-2 Cologne; Borussia
Moenchengladbach 1-1 Wolfsburg; Hamburg 2-1 Kaiserslautern;
Mainz 4-2 Hoffenheim; Nuremberg 2-1 Schalke; Stuttgart 1-2
Eintracht Frankfurt; Bayer Leverkusen 2-2 Werder Bremen;
Borussia Dortmund 2-0 Bayern Munich.  France: Monaco 0-1 Brest; Nancy 2-3 Lyon; Sochaux 3-0 Lens;
Bordeaux 1-0 Lorient; Valenciennes 2-1 Caen; Arles-Avignon 0-4
Auxerre; Saint Etienne 1-1 Marseille; Paris St. Germain 0-0
Nice; Lille 3-1 Montpellier; Rennes 3-1 Toulouse.  Netherlands: Vitesse Arnhem 0-0 Willem II; NAC Breda 2-0 NEC
Nijmegen; Excelsior 1-2 Roda JC; Ajax 1-2 FC Utrecht; Heerenveen
0-0 Den Haag; FC Twente 4-2 Groningen; AZ Alkmaar 2-1 Heracles;
